   EDITORS
   MANAGING EDITORS
   POLITICAL EDITORS
   
   Here is a tentative rundown of our Election Night copy plans for
Datastream.
   All national election stories will carry a ``p'' category and
carry the special designation ``ELN'' at the beginning of the key
word line.
   All times are EST.
   
   AM-ELN--Election Rdp, by AP Political Writer David Espo.
900-word optional add to stand throughout the night; 900-word lead
twice an hour picking up into the optional add. The story will
focus on president and cover the U.S. Senate, U.S. House and
governor races.
   AM-ELN--Senate Rdp, by Jim Drinkard. 900 words. Writethrus
hourly; more frequently during peak periods.
   AM-ELN--House Rdp, by Jill Lawrence. 900 words. Writethrus
hourly, more frequently during peak periods.
   AM-ELN--Governors Rdp, by Pete Brown. 600 words. Writethrus
hourly, or as merited.
   AM-ELN--Election Day-Scene. 900 words. A color story as voters
go to the polls. Will move mid-afternoon. No leads planned.
   Separates on Bush, Dukakis, Bentsen, Quayle, Reagan. 350 words,
two writethrus each.
   Separates on the 50 states and District of Columbia. No set-ups.
   AM-ELN--Exit Polls, by Gary Langer. Summarizes exit poll results
from the three networks. 700 words. One writethru.
   AM-ELN--Propositions Rdp, by Lee Mitgang. 600 words. Two
writethrus.
   
   Sidebars: AM-ELN--Women-Minorities. 400 words. Two writethrus.
   Election Briefs: Shorts on interesting races.
   
   The AP
