<HEAD>___</HEAD>
<HEAD>Loyal Order of Moose Pledge $1 Million For Yellowstone Recovery</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Loyal Order of Moose has placed a $50,000
deposit on its $1 million commitment to aid the restoration of the
fire-ravaged Yellowstone National Park.
   Contributions from the Moose will be used to help fund a $25
million National Park Service plan to rehabilitate damaged
facilities and restore 1,640 miles of man-made barriers used to
combat the blazes, Dennis Galvin, deputy park service director,
said Wednesday.
   Almost half of Yellowstone's 2.2 million acres were engulfed by
a series of eight fires which swept though the 100-year-old park
from June through September.
   The century-old Moose, headquartered in Mooseheart, Ill., plans
to raise funds through donations from it's lodges in 2,300
communities nationwide, said Paul J. O'Hollaren, director general
of the 1.8 million-member fraternity.
