<HEAD>Dollar Up, Stocks Rise</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The dollar inched up against the Japanese yen
Thursday, while share prices rose moderately on the Tokyo Stock
Exchange.
   The dollar closed at 127.15 yen, up 0.30 yen from Wednesday's
close of 126.85 yen. Opening at 127.46 yen, the currency moved in a
range of 127.05-127.53 yen.
   The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues, which gained
151.69 points the previous day, gained another 96.88 points, or
0.35 percent, to finish trading at 27,390.55.
   ``Despite the Dow Jones' decline of 22.58 points in New York
overnight, trading in Tokyo did pretty well,'' said an analyst with
Nomura Securities, Japan's largest brokerage.
   On the foreign exchange market, the stronger dollar followed a
rebound in oil prices and news that the U.S. government does not
want the dollar to fall further, dealers said.
