<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0371</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Thunderstorms In Oklahoma, Arizona</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Thunderstorms boomed over Oklahoma today, showers and
thunderstorms dampened southern Arizona, and low temperatures
triggered frost advisories in the Midwest.
   Showers also occurred over the eastern Great Lakes, Florida's
Atlantic coast and Louisiana.
   Temperatures were in the 20s and 30s from the upper Mississippi
Valley to the Great Lakes, the Appalachians and the northern and
middle Atlantic Coast states. A frost advisory was posted for much
of northern Indiana, and a frost and freeze advisory was issued for
the southern half of lower Michigan.
   Today's forecast called for scattered showers across the
Mississippi Valley, showers and thunderstorms from north central
Texas to Oklahoma and Arkansas, scattered showers and thunderstorms
from central and southern Arizona to southwest New Mexico and snow
ending over northern Maine.
   High temperatures were predicted in the 30s and 40s in northern
New England, the 40s from New York to northern Michigan and
northern Minnesota, the 50s from southern New England to the
mid-Atlantic States, the Ohio Valley, the mid-Mississippi Valley
and eastern sections of the Dakotas; the 80s in much of Florida,
southern Louisiana and southern Texas; the 80s and 90s across the
desert Southwest and interior valleys of California; and in the 60s
and 70s elsewhere.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 22
degrees at Watertown, N.Y., to 78 degrees at Key West, Fla.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 52 fair; Boston 39 fair; Buffalo 37 fair;
Charleston, S.C. 55 fair; Cincinnati 39 fair; Cleveland 41 partly
cloudy; Detroit 37 fair; Miami 72 fair; New York 44 fair;
Philadelphia 40 fair; Pittsburgh 36 foggy; Portland, Maine 37 fair;
Washington 43 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 42 cloudy; Chicago 40 partly cloudy;
Dallas-Fort Worth 60 drizzle; Denver 37 fair; Des Moines 43 rain;
Indianapolis 37 partly cloudy; Kansas City 44 rain; Minneapolis-St.
Paul 37 fair; Nashville 48 cloudy; New Orleans 64 cloudy; St. Louis
47 rain.
   _West: Albuquerque 52 fair; Anchorage 35 rain; Las Vegas 66
fair; Los Angeles 64 cloudy; Phoenix 75 partly cloudy; Salt Lake
City 44 fair; San Diego 66 cloudy; San Francisco 54 fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 27 fair; Toronto 34 fair.
</TEXT>
