<FILEID>AP-NR-10-20-88 1053EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r p PM-PoliticalSabotage     10-20 0298</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Political Sabotage,0308</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Democrats Says Phone Lines Were Sabotaged</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RACINE, Wis. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Wisconsin Democratic officials say they
believe the cutting of a telephone cable at the party's Racine
phone bank was an act of political sabotage.
   Fourteen telephone lines serving the phone bank were knocked out
Friday when the cable was cut on the roof, authorities said. The
line was replaced before the office reopened Saturday. Police said
Wednesday they had no leads.
   ``It's outrageous, absolutely outrageous,'' said Wisconsin
Democratic Party Chairwoman Suellen Albrecht.
   ``This is the most serious attempt (to disrupt a campaign) since
the Watergate days,'' Albrecht said. ``It brings politics in
Wisconsin to a new low.''
   The phone bank is operated by volunteers to drum up support for
presidential candidate Michael Dukakis, U.S. Senate candidate Herb
Kohl and local legislative candidates.
   Workers at the phone bank said the lines apparently were cut
shortly after the office closed Friday night.
   ``We haven't had any disgruntled employees or volunteers,'' said
Steve Morrissey, Democratic coordinator for the 1st Congressional
District. ``It was obviously someone who didn't want the phone
calls made.''
   Morrissey said the door leading to the second floor and roof was
locked Friday night.
   Wisconsin Bell installed the cable when the phone bank was
established in the mostly vacant building.
   ``Somebody knew where those wires were,'' said Marcel Dandeneau,
chairman of the Racine County Democratic Party. ``Somebody went up
there and very neatly cut the whole batch.''
   Donald Walsh, chairman of the Racine County Republican Party,
said the incident was ``stooping awfully low'' and that no local
GOP member was involved.
   ``I'm disappointed, if indeed it did happen,'' Walsh said.
``Every time an act of God or something happens, you can't run
paranoid to the fact that someone is trying to sabotage your
efforts.''
</TEXT>
