<HEAD>Reagan, a Once and Future Angelino, Roots for Dodgers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   When a reporter asked President Reagan today
if he was supporting the Los Angeles Dodgers in the World Series,
the president gave this diplomatic answer:
   ``Boy, if I were just an ordinary citizen, I sure would be.''
   The president lived in the Los Angeles area before his election
as president in 1980 and plans to live in the city after leaving
the White House in January.
   The Dodgers lead the Oakland Athletics three games to one in the
best-of-seven series.
