<HEAD>Minister Charged With Raping Confirmation Student In Church</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FERGUS FALLS, Minn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Lutheran minister has been arrested
on charges that he raped a 14-year-old confirmation student in a
church bathroom and then threatened to hurt her mother if the girl
reported it.
   The Rev. Robert Hawkinson, 68, who serves churches in western
Minnesota in Battle Lake, Henning and Amor, was scheduled for a
bond hearing today, said Otter Trail County Attorney Mike Kirk.
   The charges of first- and second-degree criminal sexual conduct
were filed Tuesday. The complaint said Hawkinson asked the girl to
stay in church after a confirmation class to discuss a situation in
her family. After their conversation, the girl went to the bathroom
and the minister followed her. There he raped her on the bathroom
floor and told her he would hurt her mother if she reported the
rape, according to the complaint.
   The attack allegedly occurred April 13 at Grace Lutheran Church
in Henning. It was reported to authorities in September ``in an
indirect sort of way'' after the alleged victim told her
girlfriend, Kirk said.
   In an interview with sheriff's deputies, Hawkinson denied the
girl's charges, Kirk said.
   ``But he asked one of the deputies, `would it be possible to do
something like that and not remember it?''' Kirk said.
</TEXT>
