<HEAD>Police Conduct Anti-Terrorist Exercises In Athens</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATHENS, Greece (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police cordoned off sections of the
capital Thursday to conduct anti-terrorist exercises, a government
spokesman said.
   The exercise tested the ability of a new anti-terrorist police
unit, said the spokesman, Sotiris Kostopoulos.
   The government has stepped up its anti-terrorism capability
after Arab gunmen opened fire on a Greek cruise ship in July,
killing nine people and injuring 98 others.
   Police also are fighting two Greek organizations _ November 17,
which claims a dozen political killings, and Revolutionary Popular
Struggle, responsible for hundreds of bombings but no deaths.
