<HEAD>Reagan Meets With Craxi</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan met with Italian Socialist
leader Bettino Craxi today and ``stressed the strong, friendly
bilateral relations between our two countries,'' the White House
said.
   Craxi, in Washington to receive an award from the
Italian-American Foundation, was prime minister of Italy from 1983
to 1987 and is now head of the Italian Socialist Party.
   White House spokesman Marlin Fitzwater said Reagan indicated
appreciation of Italy's deicison to accept the U.S. 401st Tactical
Fighter Wing, which the Spanish government had asked be moved from
Torrejon, Spain.
   Fitzwater said Reagan commended Italy's contribution to western
security and ``discussed East-West relations in general.''
   ``The president talked about the strength of NATO and how
important that is,'' the spokesman said.
   The meeting lasted about 20 minutes.
</TEXT>
