<1ST_LINE>d a AM-BRF--CocaineBaby     10-20 0169</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Cocaine Baby,0172</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Couple Face Murder Charges For Baby's Alleged Cocaine Overdose</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTA ANA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A couple have been ordered to stand
trial for murder for allegedly killing their baby daughter with a
cocaine overdose.
   A Superior Court judge Tuesday overturned a lower-court decision
and ordered Gilbert and Debbie Delgado to stand trial for the 1986
death of 2-month-old Stephanie Delgado. A municipal judge ruled
there was not enough evidence to charge the couple with murder.
   The child's death, at first linked to sudden infant death
syndrome, was later blamed on cocaine when tests found small
amounts in the child's system, authorities said.
   ``We believe that the Delgados, by selling and using large
amounts of cocaine in a very tiny apartment and in very close
proximity to a 2-month-old child, were creating an inherently
dangerous environment,'' Deputy District Attorney Richard King
said. ``It was just a matter of time before this child died of
cocaine.''
   Superior Court Judge Jean Rheinheimer set a Jan. 23 trial date.
</TEXT>
