<HEAD>Transportation Secretary Borrows Line From Quayle</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Transportation Secretary Jim Burnley, jokingly
put on the spot Thursday, borrowed Republican vice presidential
candidate Dan Quayle's answer to a question about suddenly becoming
president.
   General Motors Corp. Chairman Roger Smith, presiding at the
Economic Club luncheon, read a submitted question noting that
Burnley is 14th in line of succession to the presidency.
