<1ST_LINE>r a AM-Priest'sWritings     10-20 0514</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Priest's Writings,0529</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Excerpts From Matthew Fox's Book, `Original Blessing'</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Priest Silenced, Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   ``Original Blessing: A Primer in Creation Spirituality,'' first
published in 1983, is the Rev. Matthew Fox's best known work. Here
are some excerpts:
   
   Patriarchal religions and partiarchal paradigms for religion
have ruled the world's civilizations for at least 3,500 years. The
creation-centered tradition is feminist. Wisdom and Eros count more
than knowledge or control in such a spirituality. Together,
feminist women and men are invited to rebirth a religious vision
that is more creation-centered. And they can have fun doing it,
because play is a grace in such ritual-making and rebirthing. ...
Liberation movements are a fuller development of the cosmos' sense
of harmony, balance, justice and celebration. This is why true
spiritual liberation demands rituals of cosmic celebrating and
healing, which will in turn culminate in personal transformation
and liberation of peoples.
   
   Fall-redemption theology concentrates on sin _ yet sin, after
all, is part of the anthropomorphizing of our existence. For if the
universe is twenty billion years old, human sin is only as old as
humanity or at most four million years old. This means that
fall-redemption theology leaves out nineteen billion, nine hundred
ninty-six million years of divine-earthly history! One result of
this rather substantial lacuna is, ironically, the very
trivializing of sin, the inability to grasp sins like geocide and
ecocide and biocide of which the human race is fully capable.
   
   
   How much of the piety of ``Jesus is my best friend'' or ``Jesus
saves' comes perilously close to pure projection _ when in fact
Jesus, like all the prophets, taught peole to heal themselves and
others, to be instruments of New Creation, and to do works greater
than he did? How much of the gospel, how much of the person and
message and spirit of Jesus Christ has been lost by over
concentration on fall-redemption religion in the West?
   
   
   The universe teaches universality. Without cosmic consciousness
all universality is torn asunder and only parochialisms, ego trips
and with them institutionalized violence reign.
   
   
   It will come as no surprise to anyone to suggest that the
fall-redemption spiritual tradition which has ignored creativity as
our divine birthright and responsibility has not invested heavily
in preaching to us about the motherhood of God. The patriarchal
tradition has pretty much ignored the implications of God's
motherly side and of our responsibility to develop the mother in
ourselves, whether we are women or men, maried or celibate,
heterosexual or homosexual.
   
   
   The motherhood of God is celebrated wherever panentheism is
celebrated, where images of roundness and encircling take
precedence over linear imaging. ... In other words, the work of
every artists, divine or human-divine, is a maternal work. ... At
the same time that patriarchal society has neglected creativity and
mothering's fundamental spiritual and cultural values, it has
elevated sadomasochism to positions of glory in just about all of
our institutions, from medicine to education to religion to
government to the military to sports to business.
</TEXT>
