<DATELINE>LAS ANIMAS, Colo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A school bus carrying six children
collided with a livestock trailer Thursday and at least five people
were injured, authorities said.
   There were were few other details on the crash, which occurred
around 4:20 p.m. on U.S. 50, six miles east of of this southeastern
Colorado community, according to Dave Bridge, a State Patrol
dispatcher in Lamar.
   Six children were on the school bus, said witnesses on the scene.
   Bridge said the injured were taken to Arkansas Valley Medical
Center in La Junta, with some of them taken to Colorado Springs
hospitals via helicopters.
