them. We'll show them,' and a few of them started saying `Kill
Costas' or something like that.''
   Instead, the Dodgers took out their anger on the Athletics,
prompting Oakland manager Tony La Russa to question whether more
than the Dodgers were working against his American League champions.
   ``I'm a little aggravated right now because I heard this comment
that one of the broadcasters said on the air that the Dodgers were
the worst hitting club in the majors and that they used that in
their meeting,'' La Russa said. ``It's no big deal, but I'd like to
know how they knew about that and how they used it in the meeting.
   ``I know they were out there working, not watching TV.''
