<HEAD>Trade Fair Opens With First Communist Exhibits</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Seoul International Trade Fair
opened Thursday with the first exhibits of products from communist
nations in this country.
   The 31 nations participating in the biennial fair include Poland
and Yugoslavia, who brought samples of wine and sporting goods.
   Hong Kong companies are displaying products from China such as
carpets, electronics, chemicals and machinery.
   Seoul has been improving trade relations with communist nations.
Hungary and Yugoslavia this year exchanged trade offices with South
Korea, which has announced similar exchanges with the Soviet Union.
   Other participants included the United States, Canada, Japan,
Britian, West Germany, France, India, Pakistan, Thailand,
Indonesia, Hong Kong, Brazil and Mexico.
