<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Earns-ITT     10-20 0221</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Earns-ITT,0230</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>ITT Reports Quarterly Income Gain</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   ITT Corp., a diversified company with interests
in defense technology and insurance, on Thursday reported a 20
percent gain in third-quarter earnings over a year ago.
   Net income for the three months ended Sept. 30 totaled $230
million, or $1.60 a share, compared with restated profit of $192
million, or $1.27 a share, in the same period in 1987. Revenue was
up 9 percent, to $5.2 billion from $4.8 billion.
   The quarterly results included a one-time gain of $12 million
for tax benefits related to its Hartford Insurance Group. Last year
ITT took a $16 million charge for disposing of several investments.
   For the first nine months, ITT netted $637 million, or $4.44 per
share, compared with restated earnings of $544 million, or $3.57 a
share, in the same period last year.
   The company said the 1987 results reflected a $67 million
one-time charge in the first quarter due to an accounting change at
ITT Defense Technology. They also included a $28 million gain on
the sale of Virgin Islands Telephone Corp.
   Revenue for the first nine months rose 9 percent, to $15.5
billion from $14.3 billion in 1987.
   ITT is involved in industrial and defense technology, pulp and
timber operations and diversified services that include insurance
and hotels.
</TEXT>
