<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Earns-Caterpillar     10-20 0230</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Earns-Caterpillar,0239</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Caterpillar Reports Record Sales, Profit in Third Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PEORIA, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Caterpillar Inc. today reported record
profit and sales for the third quarter, leading company officials
to predict 1988 would be the company's best ever.
   Len Kuchan, treasurer of the Peoria-based Caterpillar, said
profit during the last three months were an unprecedented $190
million, or $1.87 per share, up 30 percent from $146 million, or
$1.47 per share, in the year-ago period.
   Sales for the quarter were $2.74 billion, up 22 percent from
$2.25 billion in the same period of 1987.
   It is the sixth consecutive quarter of profitmaking for
Peoria-based Caterpillar, the world's largest manufacturer of
earth-moving equipment, the company said. The company has reported
record sales in the last two quarters.
   ``We're pleased but this certainly does not call for
celebrating,'' Kuchan said. ``Our costs continue to be higher than
we'd like. Our profit levels are not as high as they should be
based on these sales figures.
   ``It is good news for Caterpillar, all our employees and our
community. We're going to have a good year.''
   For the first nine months of 1988, Caterpillar reported
after-tax profit of $453 million, or $4.46 a share, up about 150
percent from $180 million in the same 1987 period. Revenue was $7.6
billion vs. $5.9 billion in the nine-month period of 1987, a 28.8
percent gain.
</TEXT>
