<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Peter A. Derow, a veteran media executive, was
named Wednesday as president of Institutional Investor Inc., which
publishes Institutional Investor magazine, newsletters and books.
   The job has been held by Gilbert E. Kaplan, who will retain the
post of chairman of the Capital Cities-ABC Inc. subsidiary.
   Derow, 48, comes to Institutional Investor from Reed Publishing
