<HEAD>Holiday Corp Reports Third Quarter Gain</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEMPHIS, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Holiday Corp., a leading hotel and casino
operator, on Thursday reported a 37 percent jump in third-quarter
net income over a year ago but said its nine-month profit declined.
   Net income for the three months ended Sept. 30 was $21 million,
or 84 cents a share, compared with earnings of $15.4 million, or 63
cents, in 1987. Revenue declined to $422.1 million from $460
million.
   For the first nine months Holiday's profit totaled $102.1
million, or $4.10 a share, on revenue of $1.22 billion. That was
down from a profit of $126.7 million, or $5.21 a share, and $1.28
billion in revenue.
   Holiday said its quarterly results reflected ``strong hotel and
gaming operating results and an 18 percent reduction in interest
expense.''
   Holiday's subsidiaries include Holiday Inn, Embassy Suites,
Hampton Inn, Homewood Suites and Harrah's.
