<HEAD>Monsanto Reports 3rd Qtr. Net</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. LOUIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Monsanto Co. on Thursday reported a 16 percent
rise in its third-quarter net income as the company's agricultural
and chemical units enjoyed healthy demand for their products.
   For the quarter ended Sept. 30, earnings totaled $116 million,
or $1.67 a share, up from $100 million, or $1.30 a share a year
earlier. Revenue during the period totaled $2 billion, up from $1.9
billion a year ago.
   Agricultural and chemical results led third-quarter earnings,
the company said. Monsanto said it expects its G.D. Searle
subsidiary, acquired in 1985, to build on improved third-quarter
results and show a profit by 1989.
   For the first nine months of 1988, net income totaled $546
million, or $7.57 a share, up 39 percent from $392 million, or
$5.01 a share in the year-ago period. Revenue totaled $6.4 billion,
up from $5.8 billion for the same period in 1987.
