<HEAD>American Brands Earnings Rise 14.5 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   American Brands Inc.'s third-quarter profit rose
14.5 percent from a year earlier to a record level, the cigarette,
liquor and financial services company said Wednesday.
   American Brands, with headquarters in Old Greenwich, Conn., said
its earnings rose to $147 million, or $1.53 a share, from $128.4
million, or $1.13 a share, in the same period of 1987. Revenue rose
16 percent to $2.88 billion from $2.49 billion.
   For the first nine months, American Brands said its earnings
rose 23.3 percent to $452 million, or $4.50 a share, also a record,
from $366.6 million, or $3.22 a share. Revenue rose 17.3 percent to
$5.38 billion from $4.58 billion.
   American Brands said it was enjoying continued growth in its
cigarette business in the United States and Britain, which includes
Carlton, Lucky Strike, Pall Mall and Tareyton, as well as in its
distilled spirits business, which includes Jim Beam bourbon and
Gilbey's gin.
   Financial services had record premiums, American Brands said. It
consists of Franklin Life and Southland Life.
