<1ST_LINE>u f AM-AutoProdn     10-20 0145</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Auto Prodn,0153</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Production Goes Down This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
234,705 cars and light trucks this week, down from last week's
235,932, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago,
when 233,925 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade journal
said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 155,024 cars this week,
compared with 156,591 a week ago and 155,798 in the same week in
1987.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 79,681,
compared with last week's 79,341 and last year's 78,127.
   Canadian automakers were to build 21,559 cars this week, up from
16,866 a week ago and up from last year's 18,511.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 21,925,
compared with 18,797 a week ago and 18,151 in the same week last
year.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
