<HEAD>Kerkorian Reportedly Rejected $1 Billion MGM@UA Bid</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEVERLY HILLS, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A $1 billion bid for MGM@UA
Communications by a Monaco-based company was rejected by Kirk
Kerkorian, who owns about 80 percent of the movie company,
according to a published report Thursday.
   Elizabeth Dickenson Industries recently made the offer, said the
company's lawyer Howard Weitzman.
   But Weitzman said he didn't know if Kerkorian was uninterested
in selling or didn't want to sell at that price, the Los Angeles
Times said.
   Weitzman, attorney for the Monaco-based company, also said the
firm would have wanted former United Artists Chairman Anthony
Thomopoulos to run MGM@UA under the new ownership. Thomopoulos
resigned in September.
   Kerkorian spokesman Stephen D. Silbert declined comment.
