<FILEID>AP-NR-10-20-88 2146EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r f AM-GoodrichExpansion     10-20 0191</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Goodrich Expansion,0197</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Plans $22.9 Million Improvement At Research Plant</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRECKSVILLE, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   B.F. Goodrich Co. said Thursday it will
spend $22.9 million to expand and renovate its Brecksville research
and development center.
   The project will allow Goodrich to consolidate its headquarters
and research and development staffs for its specialty polymers and
chemicals division at the Brecksville location. Those employees are
currently located at separate sites in northeast Ohio, the company
said in a news release.
   The company's patent law office will also move from corporate
headquarters in Bath to the Brecksville facility.
   ``Our specialty polymers and chemicals business requires that
marketing and sales professionals work closely with the technical
staff to develop custom formulations for specific applications,''
said Leigh Carter, Goodrich president and chief operating officer.
``By consolidating the division's functions at one location, we
hope to foster a closer, more effective working relationship that
will improve customer service and facilitate the movement of
technology into the marketplace.''
   The project will include a new, two-story, 75,100-square-foot
building, an expansion of the main existing building and other
renovations. The improvements will be carried out over the next 18
months.
</TEXT>
